"China in the Classics," a show produced by China Media Group, examines the stirring stories of ancient Chinese classics by selecting the most outstanding of these traditional, cultural masterpieces and examining the creation process and core ideology in a form that combines cultural seminars, drama and visualization. It brings the ancient classics "alive," demonstrating Chinese wisdom, ethos and values implied in the ancient classics. Read more: 'China in the Classics' – Book of Documents 'China in the Classics': Songs of Chu 'China in the Classics' – Compendium of Materia Medica 'China in the Classics' – The Art of War 'China in the Classics' – Analects of Confucius 'China in the Classics' – Records of the Grand Historian (All photos via CMG)